# Parenting Assistant Development

- All responses must include a medical disclaimer (use `MEDICAL_DISCLAIMER` from assistantResponses.js).
- Use month-aware content from `src/data/milestones.js` when `monthUsed` is set.
- Month resolution: parsed month in query > `selectedMonth` > `currentMonth` (from birth date).
- Parse both `month 4` and `4 month` in user queries.
- Priority order: emergency (choking) > feeding > sleep > development > topic guides > fallback.
- Keep responses concise (max ~6 paragraphs in body).
- Reference AAP/WHO/CDC-style guidance; never diagnose.
- When adding topics: update `memory.md`, `assistantResponses.js`, `assistantMatch.js`, and `assistantMatch.test.js`.
- Run `npm test` and `npm run verify:data` after changes.
